benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/invoicePayments/{paymentId}/tags - Retrieve payment tags

covered: Valid Request: Happy path and multiple successful retrieval scenarios with correct 200 status and application/json.
Empty Response: 200 with empty array when payment has no tags.
Query Parameters: includeDeleted default (false) and true, audit=FULL and MINIMAL, pluginProperty (multi), combined params, invalid audit value (400), unexpected param ignored.
Path Parameter Validation: Invalid UUID (400) and non-existent payment (404).
Error Handling: 500 Internal Server Error and 503 dependency failure covered; 404 not found covered; 400 for invalid inputs covered.
Security: SQL injection in paymentId and XSS in pluginProperty handled safely.
Performance/Scalability: Heavy load and large response payload scenarios.
Resilience: Retry after transient network failure succeeds.
Compatibility/Regression: Backward compatibility of Tag schema and regression on deleted tags with includeDeleted=true.
Content Type: Response Content-Type application/json verified.
Pagination: Not applicable per API spec (no pagination parameters exposed).
gaps: Caching Behavior: No checks for ETag/Last-Modified, Cache-Control headers, or 304 on If-None-Match/If-Modified-Since.
Rate Limiting: No scenarios for burst requests or 429 Too Many Requests.
Authorization (403): No test for insufficient permissions/forbidden access.
Audit default behavior: No explicit validation that audit defaults to NONE (no audit fields) and that audit=NONE returns no audit data.
Response Schema Validation: No strict validation of Tag object structure/types and audit fields per definitions/Tag.
Query Param edge cases: includedDeleted with invalid boolean (e.g., includedDeleted=maybe) and explicit false path; case sensitivity; empty/malformed pluginProperty; URL-encoded special characters.
Content Negotiation: No tests for Accept header behavior (e.g., unsupported media type -> 406) or defaulting to JSON.
Error Response Consistency: No verification of error body schema and Content-Type for 400/404/500/503 responses.
recommendations: Add caching tests: assert ETag/Cache-Control headers; perform conditional GET with If-None-Match/If-Modified-Since expecting 304 when unchanged.
Add rate-limiting tests: send bursts to validate 429 or throttling behavior and relevant headers.
Add authorization test for 403 Forbidden when user lacks permissions/roles.
Validate audit defaults and NONE explicitly: ensure no audit fields are present when audit is omitted or set to NONE.
Introduce JSON schema validation for Tag and audit payloads to enforce field presence and types.
Expand query param edge tests: includedDeleted=false explicitly; invalid boolean values; URL-encoded pluginProperty with spaces/special chars; empty values; parameter case sensitivity handling.
Add Accept header scenarios: Accept: application/json (200) and unsupported Accept (406).
Standardize error payload checks: assert error schema fields (code/message), Content-Type application/json across 400/404/500/503.
